remarks.format:
## Remarks
`HBColor` represents a HarfBuzz color value (`hb_color_t`). HarfBuzz stores colors in BGRA byte order — `0xBBGGRRAA` — which differs from SkiaSharp's `SKColor` (`0xAARRGGBB`). Always use the named properties (<xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Red>, <xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Green>, <xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Blue>, <xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Alpha>) rather than manipulating <xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Value> directly to avoid byte-order confusion.
This is a value type; no disposal is required.
## Examples
```csharp // Construct from individual channels var red = new HBColor(red: 255, green: 0, blue: 0, alpha: 255);
// Access individual channels byte r = red.Red; // 255 byte g = red.Green; // 0 byte b = red.Blue; // 0 byte a = red.Alpha; // 255
// Convert to/from SKColor using the extension methods in SkiaSharp.HarfBuzz SKColor skRed = red.ToSKColor(); HBColor hbRed = skRed.ToHBColor(); ```
